parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls when shifting gears
the transmission slips or hesitates when accelerating
the vehicle loses power
the transmission makes a loud noise or whine
the vehicle jerks or lurches when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to stall or misfire, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or misfires
the vehicle loses power
the timing chain makes a loud noise or rattling sound
the engine check light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to lose electrical power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses electrical power
the alternator makes a loud noise or whine
the battery light comes on
the vehicle stalls or dies.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to lose visibility of essential information, such as speed, fuel level, temperature, and turning signals, which can lead to accidents or unsafe driving conditions.
symptoms: The instrument panel goes in and out
making it difficult to see essential information
the fuel gauge is not displaying correctly
the odometer reading is impossible
the temperature gauge is not working
